nno, do too much damage, should still exist.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Dramatically change the skill all together.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Let me point out that some people are trying to buy manaburn for reasons other than scoring 1 shot fungi tunics, which incidentally I don't believe happen much often, rather I think that you score whatever gear that INT caster that you just manaburned was wearing. Some people don't have AA points flying out of their ass, and let me point out that to buy MB, you need to buy MC3 first, and not the (arguably) better line of crit hits. Now, whereas I agree that it would be quite natural for a class specific skill that comes after MC3 to be something that gives you back mana, and not some nuke, that's how things are, and in my case, that's what I have been working to obtain, despite the fact I'd rather be putting my AA points into crit nukes.<br><br>If MB is completely changed (not that I say what you propose is not good, I just say it's not what I want, and it's not what I was advertised for when I started buying the MC line) then I find it quite unfair for people like me who spent their time trying to obtain something that now has disappeared, and who are left with a whooping 3 mana regen per tick for only consolation.<br><br>To close this post, I think that the point is int casters are pretty weak in PvP due to their low HPs, and whatever happens, since in EQ the damage output of _all_ classes never goes down, only up at different speeds, the people with the less HP are always going to be the first to be fucked. When everyone is dishing out ungodly amounts of DPS it's up to whoever can sustain the damage longest. <p>Aurore<HR>~Seekers of Divinity~<BR>Sorceress of <a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><a href=http://www.progressquest.com><img src=http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~bnguyen/pony.gif></img></a>The Pony with the Pointy Hat.</p><i>